data.description: A canyon oasis in the middle of the city. Nestled in a gated enclave of only 6 rarely available homes in Mission Hills. Spacious and flexible split-level layout offers a primary suite on its own floor.  Walk-in closet with newer organization system. Two more bedrooms and a bathroom on the middle level. Contemporary design features vaulted ceilings, plenty of windows bathe the space in light. A large balcony overlooking the beautiful canyon feels like you’re living atop the trees. Living spaces on separate levels from bedrooms, recently updated open kitchen and renovated bathrooms, a fireplace, Tesla charger installed in the garage, updated electrical panel, and 4.29 kWh owned solar. A ground floor bonus room (in bedroom count) that can be used for work-from-home, multi-generational living, guest quarters, home gym, etc.  Synthetic turf, outdoor living room, and fire pit in a shared side yard. Current owners paid meticulous attention to every corner of this home. A terraced hillside in back with fruit trees and room to grow your own vegetables. On the border of Mission Hills and Hillcrest, it’s walking distance to hundreds of restaurants, shopping, nightlife and more.4.29 kWh owned solar.   Tesla charger installed in the garage
